        "title": "fix(streaming): annotate empty catch blocks in stream cleanup paths",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nTwo empty `catch {}` blocks in stream cleanup paths that silently swallow I/O errors now include explanatory comments, following the same pattern established in #97701.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `src/infra/http-error-body.ts:45` — `reader.releaseLock()` after stream abort\n- `src/media/fetch.ts:460` — `reader.releaseLock()` in finally block\n\nEach catch now documents why the error is intentionally ignored (reader already released or stream already closed).\n\n## AI Assistance\n\n- AI-assisted: Yes",
